@startuml data-flow
!theme plain
title Data Flow — SSM Session, Log Ingestion, Backup

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "Operator" as op
participant "AWS API\n(IAM/STS)" as iam
participant "SSM Service" as ssm
participant "VPC Interface\nEndpoint (ssm,\nssmmessages,\nec2messages)" as vpce
participant "EC2 Instance\n(SSM Agent +\nCloudWatch Agent)" as ec2
participant "VPCE: logs\nVPCE: monitoring" as cwvpce
database "CloudWatch\nLogs + Metrics" as cw
queue "SNS Topic\n(alerts)" as sns
participant "AWS Backup\nService" as backup
database "Backup Vault\n(KMS-encrypted)" as vault

== 1. Operator session (SSM) ==

op -> iam : aws ssm start-session\n(MFA required)
iam -> iam : Validate IAM policy\n(MFA + tag conditions)
iam -> ssm : StartSession authorized
ssm -> vpce : Open data channel\n(mTLS)
vpce -> ec2 : SSM Agent receives\nsession invitation
ec2 -> vpce : Acknowledge
vpce -> ssm : Channel established
ssm -> op : Interactive shell

note right of cw
  Session activity logged to
  /aws/ssm/sessions
  (KMS-encrypted, 30d retention)
end note

ec2 --> cwvpce : Stream session log
cwvpce --> cw : Write to log group

== 2. Continuous telemetry (out-of-band) ==

ec2 -> cwvpce : PutMetricData\n(custom: mem, swap, disk)
cwvpce -> cw : Metrics ingested

ec2 -> cwvpce : PutLogEvents\n(/var/log/messages,\napp.log, audit.log)
cwvpce -> cw : Logs ingested

cw -> cw : Evaluate alarms\n(cpu, mem, disk,\nstatus, heartbeat)
cw -> sns : Alarm state change\n(if ALARM)
sns -> op : Email notification

== 3. Daily backup (05:00 UTC) ==

backup -> backup : Backup plan trigger\n(cron 05:00 UTC)
backup -> backup : Tag selection:\nBackup=daily
backup -> ec2 : Create snapshot\n(EBS volume)
ec2 -> backup : Snapshot ID
backup -> vault : Store recovery point\n(encrypted with platform CMK)

note right of vault
  Lifecycle:
  • Warm: days 1-7
  • Cold: days 8-97
  • Delete: day 98+
end note

backup -> sns : Job state change\n(only on FAILED/EXPIRED)
sns --> op : Email if failure

== 4. Restore (manual, on-demand) ==

op -> iam : Assume break-glass role\n(triggers EventBridge alert)
iam -> backup : StartRestoreJob
backup -> vault : Read recovery point
vault -> backup : Encrypted snapshot
backup -> ec2 : Create new EBS volume\n(re-encrypted with CMK)
ec2 -> op : Volume available for attach

@enduml
